Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_add_target_pg_mode(25.10)                    set_add_target_pg_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_add_target_pg_mode  -  Sets  global variables for the add_target_pg
       command

Syntax
        set_add_target_pg_mode

       [-help]

       [-allow_weak_connect {true | false}]

       [-max_extension_distance <value>]

       [-pins {<cell1>:<pin1> <cell1>:<pin2> <cell2>:<pin1> ...}]

       [-pins_group_distance <value>]

       [-reset]

       [-respect_routes {none | fixed | fixed_and_clock | all}]

       [-share_resource {true | false}]

       Sets global variables for the add_target_pg command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each set_add_target_pg_mode parameter. For a de-
              tailed  description  of  the command and all its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man set_add_target_pg_mode

       -allow_weak_connect {true | false}
              When this parameter is set to false, the number of wires created
              on every stack layer need to satisfy the defined count with  DRC
              clean. Else, the PG pin is left open.

              When  set to true, the count lesser than defined can also be ac-
              cepted while creating the total count causing DRC.

              Default: false

       -max_extension_distance <value>
              Specifies the maximum distance that the target PG pin can extend
              to the target layer. If the distance between the target  PG  pin
              and  the  candidate  target layer is lesser than or equal to the
              specified distance, the candidate target is treated as the  real
              target.

              If the target PG wire cannot be found within -max_extension_dis-
              tance, the instance is left open. If this parameter is not used,
              the  software connects the stripe layer to the closest target PG
              wire with DRC clean, by default. See the figure below for under-
              standing:

              Default: 2147483647

       -pins {<cell1>:<pin1> <cell1>:<pin2> <cell2>:<pin1> ...}
              Specifies the cell pins to be connected.

              Default: ""

       -pins_group_distance <value>
              Specifies the side-to-side distance of the pins to be treated as
              a group while connecting the target PG pins. The pins  belonging
              to the same group share the same target PG stripes connection.

              When  this  parameter  is  set  to  its default value, auto, the
              add_target_pg command uses the default  behavior  of  target  PG
              generation  to  group  the pins. If this parameter is not speci-
              fied, the software uses the pitch of metal layer above the  pins
              layer with same direction (layer_pin+2) as the group distance.

              If  the  pitch of metal layer above the pins layer with the same
              direction (layer_pin+2) is not defined, the pins  will  be  con-
              nected separately.

              If  the distance between two pins is lesser than group_distance,
              they will be treated as one group. See the figure below for  un-
              derstanding:

              When  pins_group_distance  is not defined, the software uses the
              pitch of the metal layer above the pins layer with the same  di-
              rection  (layer_pin+2) as the group distance. See the figure be-
              low for understanding:

              The following figure presents how the target PG pin's horizontal
              offset affects the stapling sharing:

              Default: auto

       -reset Resets all or specified parameters to their default values.

       -respect_routes {none | fixed | fixed_and_clock | all}
              Specifies the route types to respect for DRC check during target
              PG generation. This parameter always honor all covers  and  PGs,
              but does not honor the trail routes, Following are the parameter
              values:

              * none: Specifies that no route types are respected.

              * fixed: Respects fixed regular wires.

              * fixed_and_clock: Respects fixed and routed clocks.

              * all:  Respects  fixed  and routed clocks along with the routed
                signals.

              For  more  information  on  the  support  of  the   set_add_tar-
              get_pg_mode  -respect_route  parameter  values with various sta-
              tuses  of  net,  see  Support  of  set_add_target_pg_mode   -re-
              spect_route Parameter Values.

              Default: fixed_and_clock

       -share_resource {true | false}
              When  set  to  true,  the  newly  added  PGs of the intermediate
              stacked layer can connect to the existing PG wire  of  the  same
              layers  and  are preferred to be shifted to the track of the ex-
              isting PG to save the track resource. If there are DRCs  between
              the  added  PG  and the existing PG after shifting, the added PG
              will follow the behavior explained below:

              * If the added wire is on different net from the existing PG, it
                will be shifted again to avoid DRC.

              * If the added wire is on the same net of the  existing  PG,  it
                will be merged with the existing wire.

              When  set  to false, the stacked layer cannot connect to the ex-
              isting intermediate layers between the cell PG pin and target PG
              layer. Additionally, the newly added PG will be shifted  if  its
              original location causes DRC.

              Default: true

